Map and enable the Berlin2CD pBridge resource without configuring its
channels or submitting descriptors. Report only side-effect-free semaphore,
dHub, reset and BCM registers so the bootloader state can be compared with
Valve's driver before active DMA work begins.

The pBridge clock follows the NFC clocks across probe, suspend, resume and
removal. The controller remains probe-only. There is no TCM access, channel
initialization, NAND page read, MTD registration, erase or program
operation.

